-- Deutsche Post Signs Agreement With Banks for $2.6 Billion Syndicated Loan
-- B y   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-12-22T08:15:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/deutsche-post-signs-agreement-with-banks-for-2-6-billion-syndicated-loan.html
Deutsche Post AG said it has agreed
upon a 2 billion-euro revolving syndicated loan with a group of
German and international banks. It replaces previous bilateral
credit lines, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
